OL,3,CWelfare cuts - what changes has the
OL,4,Cgovernment made and will they appease
OL,5,CMPs?
OL,7,FThe government had planned to freeze
OL,8,Fthe health top-up of universal credit
OL,9,Ffor existing claimants until 2030, but
OL,10,Fafter the backlash payments for
OL,11,Fcurrent recipients will now rise with
OL,12,Finflation.
OL,14,FPeople with a limited capacity to work
OL,15,Fbecause of a disability or long term
OL,16,Fsickness, get a universal credit top-
OL,17,Fup payment of #416.19 a month.
OL,19,FBut for new claimants from 2026, the
OL,20,Fpayments will be cut in half, from #97
OL,21,Fa week to #50 a week in 2026-2027.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
